 valuable thing-specific with (plant-related) crops often 
 among the most intensively produced. The higher 
 value of (plant-related) crops relative to staple foods is 
 a key factor. A comparison of mean monthly tomato 
 and staple food prices in the Yaounde market in recent 
 years illustrates the 'high value' nature of (plant-related) crops common to many African food markets 
 (Fig. 1). 
 To help farming-based (process by which something becomes stronger or worse) in Africa, 
 better understanding is needed of those examples 
 where the process has already taken hold. Adding/giving towards that end, this paper examines the adoption 
 of stronger monocrop systems of (plant-related) production among smallholders in southern Cameroon. 
